    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/figure-table-interpretation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 provides an intuitive graphical user interface with six views... including views for CSI:FingerID results and predicted fingerprints... Results can be filtered on the basis of XlogP values... SIRIUS 4 also displays all databases where each structure candidate can be found... The user interface offers additional filtering options, but also full text search for every output list.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS and CSI:FingerID produce candidate structures and fragmentation trees with visualization and filtering capabilities. However, CANOPUS and MSNovelist are not mentioned in the paper, so the scope claim is only partially supported for the tools actually discussed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-019-0344-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "figure-table-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When SIRIUS, CSI:FingerID, CANOPUS, or MSNovelist has produced candidate molecular structures, chemical classifications, or fragmentation tree visualizations and you need to evaluate which candidates are most likely correct, understand the chemical class assignments, or extract m",
