    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/reproducibility-gap-detection/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 is written in Java; is open source under the GNU General Public License (version 3); and works on Windows, macOS X, and Linux... a source copy is hosted on Git Hub (https://github.com/boecker-lab/sirius).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SIRIUS 4 as open-source and available on GitHub, and extensively documents methods (fragmentation trees, isotope pattern analysis, molecular formula determination). However, the paper does NOT explicitly frame its contribution as a 'reproducibility gap detection' task or methodology. The card's research question appears to be a meta-analytical framework for assessing gaps, whereas the paper is a tool paper describing SIRIUS 4 implementation itself. The paper does document implementation details but not as a gap-detection exercise.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-019-0344-8",
